{{etyl|ang}} ''[[healf]]'' ('half'); as a noun, 'half', 'side', 'part'; akin to Old Saxon, Old Friesian, and Dutch ''[[half#Dutch|half]]'', German ''[[halb]]'', Swedish ''[[half#Swedish|half]]'', Danish ''[[halv]]'', Icelandic ''[[hālfr]]'' and Gothic [[𐌷𐌰𐌻𐌱𐍃]] (halbs). Compare ''[[halve]]'', ''[[behalf]]''.

